# Get In Water — Firebase setup (one-time, in Firebase Console)
#
# 1. Create a project at https://console.firebase.google.com
# 2. Authentication → Sign-in method → Enable Google
# 3. Firestore → Create database (production mode) → deploy firestore.rules from this repo
# 4. Project settings → Your apps → Add Web app → copy config into firebase-config.js
# 5. Authentication → Google → copy Web client ID into GIW_FIREBASE_WEB_CLIENT_ID
# 6. Add Android app (package com.threecats.lsp.getinwater) → download google-services.json
#    → place at android/app/google-services.json (do not commit; use CI secret for builds)
# 7. Add SHA-1 fingerprints (debug + release) in Firebase → Android app settings
# 8. Authorized domains: threecats-lsp.com, localhost
#
# GitHub Actions (APK builds): add secret GOOGLE_SERVICES_JSON = base64 of google-services.json
#
#   PowerShell: [Convert]::ToBase64String([IO.File]::ReadAllBytes("android\app\google-services.json"))
#
# Optional but recommended — pin CI debug keystore so SHA-1 stays the same every build:
# 1. After one APK workflow run, download artifact "android-debug-keystore"
# 2. Add secret ANDROID_DEBUG_KEYSTORE = base64 of that debug.keystore file
#
#   PowerShell: [Convert]::ToBase64String([IO.File]::ReadAllBytes("debug.keystore"))
